50class ValueSerializer {
51 public:
52 ValueSerializer(Isolate* isolate, v8::ValueSerializer::Delegate* delegate);
53 ~ValueSerializer();
54 ValueSerializer(const ValueSerializer&) = delete;
55 ValueSerializer& operator=(const ValueSerializer&) = delete;
56
57 /*
58 * Writes out a header, which includes the format version.
59 */
60 void WriteHeader();
61
62 /*
63 * Serializes a V8 object into the buffer.
64 */
65 Maybe<bool> WriteObject(Handle<Object> object) V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
66
67 /*
68 * Returns the buffer, allocated via the delegate, and its size.
69 * Caller assumes ownership of the buffer.
70 */
71 std::pair<uint8_t*, size_t> Release();
72
73 /*
74 * Marks an ArrayBuffer as havings its contents transferred out of band.
75 * Pass the corresponding JSArrayBuffer in the deserializing context to
76 * ValueDeserializer::TransferArrayBuffer.
77 */
78 void TransferArrayBuffer(uint32_t transfer_id,
79 Handle<JSArrayBuffer> array_buffer);
80
81 /*
82 * Publicly exposed wire format writing methods.
83 * These are intended for use within the delegate's WriteHostObject method.
84 */
85 void WriteUint32(uint32_t value);
86 void WriteUint64(uint64_t value);
87 void WriteRawBytes(const void* source, size_t length);
88 void WriteDouble(double value);
89 void WriteByte(uint8_t value);
90
91 /*
92 * Indicate whether to treat ArrayBufferView objects as host objects,
93 * i.e. pass them to Delegate::WriteHostObject. This should not be
94 * called when no Delegate was passed.
95 *
96 * The default is not to treat ArrayBufferViews as host objects.
97 */
98 void SetTreatArrayBufferViewsAsHostObjects(bool mode);
99
100 private:
101 // Managing allocations of the internal buffer.
102 Maybe<bool> ExpandBuffer(size_t required_capacity);
103
104 // Writing the wire format.
105 void WriteTag(SerializationTag tag);
106 template <typename T>
107 void WriteVarint(T value);
108 template <typename T>
109 void WriteZigZag(T value);
110 void WriteOneByteString(base::Vector<const uint8_t> chars);
111 void WriteTwoByteString(base::Vector<const base::uc16> chars);
112 void WriteBigIntContents(Tagged<BigInt> bigint);
113 Maybe<uint8_t*> ReserveRawBytes(size_t bytes);
114
115 // Writing V8 objects of various kinds.
116 void WriteOddball(Tagged<Oddball> oddball);
117 void WriteSmi(Tagged<Smi> smi);
118 void WriteHeapNumber(Tagged<HeapNumber> number);
119 void WriteBigInt(Tagged<BigInt> bigint);
120 void WriteString(Handle<String> string);
121 Maybe<bool> WriteJSReceiver(Handle<JSReceiver> receiver)
122 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
123 Maybe<bool> WriteJSObject(Handle<JSObject> object) V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
124 Maybe<bool> WriteJSObjectSlow(Handle<JSObject> object) V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
125 Maybe<bool> WriteJSArray(Handle<JSArray> array) V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
126 void WriteJSDate(Tagged<JSDate> date);
127 Maybe<bool> WriteJSPrimitiveWrapper(Handle<JSPrimitiveWrapper> value)
128 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
129 void WriteJSRegExp(Handle<JSRegExp> regexp);
130 Maybe<bool> WriteJSMap(Handle<JSMap> map) V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
131 Maybe<bool> WriteJSSet(Handle<JSSet> map) V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
132 Maybe<bool> WriteJSArrayBuffer(Handle<JSArrayBuffer> array_buffer)
133 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
134 Maybe<bool> WriteJSArrayBufferView(Tagged<JSArrayBufferView> array_buffer);
135 Maybe<bool> WriteJSError(Handle<JSObject> error) V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
136 Maybe<bool> WriteJSSharedArray(Handle<JSSharedArray> shared_array)
137 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
138 Maybe<bool> WriteJSSharedStruct(Handle<JSSharedStruct> shared_struct)
139 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
140#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
141 Maybe<bool> WriteWasmModule(Handle<WasmModuleObject> object)
142 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
143 Maybe<bool> WriteWasmMemory(Handle<WasmMemoryObject> object)
144 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
145#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
146 Maybe<bool> WriteSharedObject(Handle<HeapObject> object)
147 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
148 Maybe<bool> WriteHostObject(Handle<JSObject> object) V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
149
150 /*
151 * Reads the specified keys from the object and writes key-value pairs to the
152 * buffer. Returns the number of keys actually written, which may be smaller
153 * if some keys are not own properties when accessed.
154 */
155 Maybe<uint32_t> WriteJSObjectPropertiesSlow(
156 Handle<JSObject> object, Handle<FixedArray> keys) V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
157
158 Maybe<bool> IsHostObject(Handle<JSObject> object);
159
160 /*
161 * Asks the delegate to handle an error that occurred during data cloning, by
162 * throwing an exception appropriate for the host.
163 */
164 V8_NOINLINE Maybe<bool> ThrowDataCloneError(MessageTemplate template_index)
165 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
166 V8_NOINLINE Maybe<bool> ThrowDataCloneError(MessageTemplate template_index,
167 DirectHandle<Object> arg0)
168 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
169
170 Maybe<bool> ThrowIfOutOfMemory();
171
172 Isolate* const isolate_;
173 v8::ValueSerializer::Delegate* const delegate_;
174 uint8_t* buffer_ = nullptr;
175 size_t buffer_size_ = 0;
176 size_t buffer_capacity_ = 0;
177 bool has_custom_host_objects_ = false;
178 bool treat_array_buffer_views_as_host_objects_ = false;
179 bool out_of_memory_ = false;
180 Zone zone_;
181
182 // To avoid extra lookups in the identity map, ID+1 is actually stored in the
183 // map (checking if the used identity is zero is the fast way of checking if
184 // the entry is new).
185 IdentityMap<uint32_t, ZoneAllocationPolicy> id_map_;
186 uint32_t next_id_ = 0;
187
188 // A similar map, for transferred array buffers.
189 IdentityMap<uint32_t, ZoneAllocationPolicy> array_buffer_transfer_map_;
190
191 // The conveyor used to keep shared objects alive.
192 SharedObjectConveyorHandles* shared_object_conveyor_ = nullptr;
193};

195/*
196 * Deserializes values from data written with ValueSerializer, or a compatible
197 * implementation.
198 */
199class ValueDeserializer {
200 public:
201 ValueDeserializer(Isolate* isolate, base::Vector<const uint8_t> data,
202 v8::ValueDeserializer::Delegate* delegate);
203 ValueDeserializer(Isolate* isolate, const uint8_t* data, size_t size);
204 ~ValueDeserializer();
205 ValueDeserializer(const ValueDeserializer&) = delete;
206 ValueDeserializer& operator=(const ValueDeserializer&) = delete;
207
208 /*
209 * Runs version detection logic, which may fail if the format is invalid.
210 */
211 Maybe<bool> ReadHeader() V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
212
213 /*
214 * Reads the underlying wire format version. Likely mostly to be useful to
215 * legacy code reading old wire format versions. Must be called after
216 * ReadHeader.
217 */
218 uint32_t GetWireFormatVersion() const { return version_; }
219
220 /*
221 * Deserializes a V8 object from the buffer.
222 */
223 MaybeHandle<Object> ReadObjectWrapper() V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
224
225 /*
226 * Reads an object, consuming the entire buffer.
227 *
228 * This is required for the legacy "version 0" format, which did not allow
229 * reference deduplication, and instead relied on a "stack" model for
230 * deserializing, with the contents of objects and arrays provided first.
231 */
232 MaybeHandle<Object> ReadObjectUsingEntireBufferForLegacyFormat()
233 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
234
235 /*
236 * Accepts the array buffer corresponding to the one passed previously to
237 * ValueSerializer::TransferArrayBuffer.
238 */
239 void TransferArrayBuffer(uint32_t transfer_id,
240 Handle<JSArrayBuffer> array_buffer);
241
242 /*
243 * Publicly exposed wire format writing methods.
244 * These are intended for use within the delegate's WriteHostObject method.
245 */
246 bool ReadUint32(uint32_t* value) V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
247 bool ReadUint64(uint64_t* value) V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
248 bool ReadDouble(double* value) V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
249 bool ReadRawBytes(size_t length, const void** data) V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
250 bool ReadByte(uint8_t* value) V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
251
252 private:
253 // Reading the wire format.
254 Maybe<SerializationTag> PeekTag() const V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
255 void ConsumeTag(SerializationTag peeked_tag);
256 Maybe<SerializationTag> ReadTag() V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
257 template <typename T>
258 V8_INLINE Maybe<T> ReadVarint() V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
259 template <typename T>
260 V8_NOINLINE Maybe<T> ReadVarintLoop() V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
261 template <typename T>
262 Maybe<T> ReadZigZag() V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
263 Maybe<double> ReadDouble() V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
264 Maybe<base::Vector<const uint8_t>> ReadRawBytes(size_t size)
265 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
266 MaybeHandle<Object> ReadObject() V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
267
268 // Reads a string if it matches the one provided.
269 // Returns true if this was the case. Otherwise, nothing is consumed.
270 bool ReadExpectedString(Handle<String> expected) V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
271
272 // Like ReadObject, but skips logic for special cases in simulating the
273 // "stack machine".
274 MaybeHandle<Object> ReadObjectInternal() V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
275
276 // Reads a string intended to be part of a more complicated object.
277 // Before v12, these are UTF-8 strings. After, they can be any encoding
278 // permissible for a string (with the relevant tag).
279 MaybeHandle<String> ReadString() V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
280
281 // Reading V8 objects of specific kinds.
282 // The tag is assumed to have already been read.
283 MaybeHandle<BigInt> ReadBigInt() V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
284 MaybeHandle<String> ReadUtf8String(
285 AllocationType allocation = AllocationType::kYoung) V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
286 MaybeHandle<String> ReadOneByteString(
287 AllocationType allocation = AllocationType::kYoung) V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
288 MaybeHandle<String> ReadTwoByteString(
289 AllocationType allocation = AllocationType::kYoung) V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
290 MaybeHandle<JSObject> ReadJSObject() V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
291 MaybeHandle<JSArray> ReadSparseJSArray() V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
292 MaybeHandle<JSArray> ReadDenseJSArray() V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
293 MaybeHandle<JSDate> ReadJSDate() V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
294 MaybeHandle<JSPrimitiveWrapper> ReadJSPrimitiveWrapper(SerializationTag tag)
295 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
296 MaybeHandle<JSRegExp> ReadJSRegExp() V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
297 MaybeHandle<JSMap> ReadJSMap() V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
298 MaybeHandle<JSSet> ReadJSSet() V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
299 MaybeHandle<JSArrayBuffer> ReadJSArrayBuffer(
300 bool is_shared, bool is_resizable) V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
301 MaybeHandle<JSArrayBuffer> ReadTransferredJSArrayBuffer()
302 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
303 MaybeHandle<JSArrayBufferView> ReadJSArrayBufferView(
304 Handle<JSArrayBuffer> buffer) V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
305 bool ValidateJSArrayBufferViewFlags(
306 Tagged<JSArrayBuffer> buffer, uint32_t serialized_flags,
307 bool& is_length_tracking, bool& is_backed_by_rab) V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
308 MaybeHandle<Object> ReadJSError() V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
309#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
310 MaybeHandle<JSObject> ReadWasmModuleTransfer() V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
311 MaybeHandle<WasmMemoryObject> ReadWasmMemory() V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
312#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
313 MaybeHandle<HeapObject> ReadSharedObject() V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
314 MaybeHandle<JSObject> ReadHostObject() V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
315
316 /*
317 * Reads key-value pairs into the object until the specified end tag is
318 * encountered. If successful, returns the number of properties read.
319 */
320 Maybe<uint32_t> ReadJSObjectProperties(Handle<JSObject> object,
321 SerializationTag end_tag,
322 bool can_use_transitions);
323
324 // Manipulating the map from IDs to reified objects.
325 bool HasObjectWithID(uint32_t id);
326 MaybeHandle<JSReceiver> GetObjectWithID(uint32_t id);
327 void AddObjectWithID(uint32_t id, Handle<JSReceiver> object);
328
329 Isolate* const isolate_;
330 v8::ValueDeserializer::Delegate* const delegate_;
331 const uint8_t* position_;
332 const uint8_t* const end_;
333 uint32_t version_ = 0;
334 uint32_t next_id_ = 0;
335 bool version_13_broken_data_mode_ = false;
336 bool suppress_deserialization_errors_ = false;
337
338 // Always global handles.
339 Handle<FixedArray> id_map_;
340 MaybeHandle<SimpleNumberDictionary> array_buffer_transfer_map_;
341
342 // The conveyor used to keep shared objects alive.
343 const SharedObjectConveyorHandles* shared_object_conveyor_ = nullptr;
344};
